official_title: A bill to transfer jurisdiction of certain public lands in the State of Utah to the Forest Service, and for other purposes.

summary.text: Fishlake National Forest Enlargement Act - Transfers jurisdiction of certain public lands in Utah, currently under the jurisdiction of the Bureau of Land Management, to the Secretary of Agriculture to be added to, and administered by the Secretary as part of, the Fishlake National Forest. Extends current land use authorizations with respect to such transferred lands.
